[src:abortion-in-south-carolina/abortion-in-alaska] In 2017, the state had an infant mortality rate of 5.6 deaths per 1,000 live births.
[src:abortion-in-south-carolina/abortion-in-alaska] 17 US states, including Alaska, use their own funds to cover all or most "medically necessary" abortions sought by low-income women under Medicaid, 13 of which are required by State court orders to do so.
[src:abortion-in-south-carolina/abortion-in-alaska] In 2010, the state had 835 publicly funded abortions, all of which were state funded.
[src:abortion-in-south-carolina/abortion-in-alaska] Women from the state participated in marches supporting abortion rights as part of a #StoptheBans movement in May 2019.
[src:abortion-in-south-carolina/abortion-in-alaska] Hundreds of women attended a rally in Anchorage at Town Square Park to protest legislation proposed in Alaska's House to restrict abortion rights.
[src:abortion-in-south-carolina/abortion-in-alaska] The event was organized by Planned Parenthood Votes and Alaska ACLU.
[src:abortion-in-south-carolina/abortion-in-alaska] There was another rally at the Alaska Capitol in Juneau in May 2019, in opposition to the bill proposed by Republican Rep.
